{"nodes": [{"id": "cad_tactus_chest_plate", "label": "tactus_chest_plate.scad \u2014 body-contoured plate holding 6 string drivers", "file_type": "code", "source_file": "cad/tactus_chest_plate.scad", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Cylindrical-section torso shell carrying a vertical column of 6 self-adjusting driver sockets (high-E top to low-E bottom). drv_dia was just set to 52 (\u00d852 web-verified, Havit HV-SK473) replacing the placeholder; depth(27)/magnet(30) and torso_r(150)/col_pitch(46) remain PLACEHOLDERS until the wearer + vest are measured, then re-render in OpenSCAD. Prints as 2 tiles to fit the bed and flex to the body. use <tactus_socket.scad> for socket geometry."}, {"id": "cad_tactus_chest_plate_shell", "label": "shell() \u2014 curved torso-cylinder shell panel between z_lo..z_hi", "file_type": "code", "source_file": "cad/tactus_chest_plate.scad", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "A front section of the torso cylinder: difference of two cylinders (torso_r + plate_t outer, torso_r inner) intersected with an arc_half-wide chord box. Modeled from z=0 and translated by tile()."}, {"id": "cad_tactus_chest_plate_socket_at", "label": "socket_at(z) \u2014 places a driver_socket on the inner face at height z", "file_type": "code", "source_file": "cad/tactus_chest_plate.scad", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Positions a shared driver_socket(drv_dia=52, drv_depth, drv_mag_dia) on the front inner face, skin-side toward the body. The \u00d852 fit is delegated to tactus_socket.scad's driver_socket()."}, {"id": "cad_tactus_chest_plate_bore_at", "label": "bore_at(z) \u2014 through-hole so the cone/button reaches skin", "file_type": "code", "source_file": "cad/tactus_chest_plate.scad", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "\u00d8(drv_dia - 8) = \u00d844 through-bore in the panel at height z so the cone/contact button protrudes toward the body."}, {"id": "cad_tactus_chest_plate_strap_slots", "label": "strap_slots(z_lo, z_hi) \u2014 edge slots to lash onto the laser-tag vest", "file_type": "code", "source_file": "cad/tactus_chest_plate.scad", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Cuts strap slots along the top and bottom edges (3 across each) for lashing the plate to the laser-tag vest chest panel."}, {"id": "cad_tactus_chest_plate_tile", "label": "tile(z_lo, z_hi) \u2014 one print tile (shell + sockets - bores - slots)", "file_type": "code", "source_file": "cad/tactus_chest_plate.scad", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Builds one tile by unioning the translated shell with the sockets whose z falls in range, then subtracting bores and strap slots. Uses translated shell() (relative-z modeling); tile_abs() is the absolute-coordinate alternative."}, {"id": "cad_tactus_chest_plate_tile_abs", "label": "tile_abs(z_lo, z_hi) \u2014 print tile built at absolute z coordinates", "file_type": "code", "source_file": "cad/tactus_chest_plate.scad", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "The actually-rendered tile builder: inlines the shell geometry at absolute z (rather than translating shell()) so sockets land at correct absolute heights, then subtracts bore_at and strap_slots. Driven by part = full | top | bottom."}], "edges": [{"source": "cad_tactus_chest_plate", "target": "cad_tactus_chest_plate_shell", "relation": "calls", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "cad/tactus_chest_plate.scad", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "cad_tactus_chest_plate", "target": "cad_tactus_chest_plate_socket_at", "relation": "calls", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "cad/tactus_chest_plate.scad", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "cad_tactus_chest_plate", "target": "cad_tactus_chest_plate_bore_at", "relation": "calls", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "cad/tactus_chest_plate.scad", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "cad_tactus_chest_plate", "target": "cad_tactus_chest_plate_strap_slots", "relation": "calls", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "cad/tactus_chest_plate.scad", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "cad_tactus_chest_plate", "target": "cad_tactus_chest_plate_tile", "relation": "calls", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "cad/tactus_chest_plate.scad", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "cad_tactus_chest_plate", "target": "cad_tactus_chest_plate_tile_abs", "relation": "calls", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "cad/tactus_chest_plate.scad", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "cad_tactus_chest_plate_tile", "target": "cad_tactus_chest_plate_shell", "relation": "calls", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "cad/tactus_chest_plate.scad", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "cad_tactus_chest_plate_tile", "target": "cad_tactus_chest_plate_socket_at", "relation": "calls", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "cad/tactus_chest_plate.scad", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "cad_tactus_chest_plate_tile", "target": "cad_tactus_chest_plate_bore_at", "relation": "calls", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "cad/tactus_chest_plate.scad", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "cad_tactus_chest_plate_tile", "target": "cad_tactus_ches